From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: 2026-05-25T22:00:00Z
Subject: [PATCH] patches/0065-fman-pcd-graft-kernel-scheme.patch

ASK2 v1.1-B (2026-05-25): resurrect the PR14z13 graft API.  Fixes the
M2 kernel-net CPU regression by GRAFTING the ASK CC tree onto the
existing kernel-owned KG scheme on each port, instead of allocating
a NEW scheme that loses the FMan KG dispatch race.

Root cause (verified on hardware 2026-05-25 via bin/ask-pcd-regdump.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Path A (patches 0044/0049/0050/0060/0061) installs its pre-netdev
hook successfully — 10 cc_v4_tcp+cc_v4_udp installs, 60 dedup hits,
70 echo-skips, zero error paths.  Post-burst regdump shows ASK's
schemes 5..9 are programmed correctly:

    Scheme 8 (ASK, eth3 port 0x10):
        kgse_mv   = 0x001c0006 (5-tuple)
        kgse_ccbs = 0x0004d300 (valid CC tree group-table offset)
        kgse_spc  = 0           <- NEVER COUNTS

The kernel dpaa_eth driver's keygen_port_hashing_init() allocated
schemes 0..4 at MAC probe time BEFORE ask.ko's fs_initcall fired:

    Scheme 3 (kernel, eth3 port 0x10):
        kgse_mv   = 0x00180000 (IPSRC1|IPDST1 hash)
        kgse_ccbs = 0           <- DIRECT BMI ENQ, no CC walk
        kgse_spc  = 18,017,267  <- CONSUMES EVERY FRAME

FMan KG silicon arbitration (RM §8.7.4): when multiple schemes are
bound to the same hwport via fmkg_pe_sp, the LOWEST scheme ID wins
per-packet.  Scheme 3 < Scheme 8 → kernel always wins → ASK's CC
tree is dispatched-to never.

M2 verdict before this patch: throughput PASS 6.95 Gbps, kernel-net
CPU FAIL 30.51 % (target ≤ 5 %).

Architectural fix (Option A from the PR14z13 decision matrix)
-------------------------------------------------------------
ASK does NOT create new KG schemes.  Instead, ASK GRAFTS its CC tree
onto the EXISTING kernel-owned scheme via KGSE_CCBS programming.
The kernel scheme's parser/extract recipe (IPSRC1|IPDST1 hash) stays
unchanged; only KGSE_CCBS is updated to point at ASK's CC tree.

CC tree's miss-action = FORWARD_FQ(kernel_scheme->base_fqid)
preserves the kernel's per-CPU RX hash for unmatched frames (ARP,
SYN, ICMP, VPP AF_XDP control plane) exactly as if no PCD chain
were present.

KGSE_MODE handling
------------------
This patch leaves KGSE_MODE UNTOUCHED.  Cross-checked against the
legacy QorIQ SDK USDPAA reference (tmp-mono-ask/.../999-layerscape-
ask-kernel_linux_5_4_3_00_0.patch lines 13838-13844), which keeps
NIA = BMI|ENQ_FRAME (0x500002) when grafting to CC and ORs in
CCOBASE bits[30:24].  CC walking on FMan v3 is implicit when
KGSE_CCBS is non-zero — the gating bit was a v2-era control that
v3 collapsed into the all-zero CCBS check.

The previously-archived companion patch 0043 (PR14z15) tried to
flip the NIA engine from BMI to FM_CTL inside keygen_scheme_set_ccbs;
hardware verification 2026-05-23 disproved that hypothesis (the
kernel's working schemes 0/1/2 have kgse_mode=0x80500002 and
kgse_ccbs=0 actively counting; the NIA-flipped grafted schemes
3/4 stalled with kgse_spc≈0).  Patch 0051 reverted 0043.  This
patch resurrects ONLY 0042 (KGSE_CCBS-only RMW), not 0043.

This patch
----------
Resurrects the three public ABI entry points from
archive-grafted-2026-05-24/0042-fman-pcd-kg-graft-cc.patch:

  fman_pcd_kg_lookup_port_scheme(pcd, port_id, &sid, &base_fqid)
    Reads fmkg_pe.fmkg_pe_sp[port_id] via AR-mediated indirect
    access, returns the LOWEST scheme ID bound to that hwport
    (which is the scheme FMan KG will actually dispatch to per
    packet) and that scheme's KGSE_FQB base_fqid (so CC miss can
    fall back to it).  Returns -ENOENT if no scheme is bound.

  fman_pcd_kg_graft_cc(pcd, scheme_id, cc_tree)
    AR-mediated RMW on KGSE_CCBS of the named scheme, setting it
    to cc_tree's group_table_off.  Scheme MUST already be in
    'used' state.

  fman_pcd_kg_ungraft_cc(pcd, scheme_id)
    Symmetric inverse: clears KGSE_CCBS back to 0.  Idempotent.

The ASK-side rewrite of ask_pcd_install_hook() to call
lookup_port_scheme + graft_cc instead of scheme_create + attach_cc
+ bind_port is a separate direct edit to
kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ask_hw.c (the OOT module is
edited in-source, not via patch — same pattern as every other
ask_*.c file in this repo).

Verification plan
-----------------
1. patch-health.sh --flavor ask --source release: Pass=51 Fail=0.
2. ISO build via bin/local-build.sh ask: succeeds, ask.ko vermagic
   matches kernel.
3. On hardware after deploy:
   - bin/ask-pcd-regdump.py shows kgse_ccbs != 0 on kernel schemes
     3 and 4 (the FMan ports bound to eth3 and eth4 SFP+).
   - kgse_spc on schemes 3+4 keeps incrementing (parser still
     walking these schemes).
   - kgse_spc on schemes 5..9 stays 0 (ASK no longer creates them).
   - bin/verify-ask-flow-offload.sh: throughput ≥ 7 Gbps,
     kernel-net CPU ≤ 5 % → M2 hard gate PASS.
